# qactl repo rules

## The agent-shaped contract (don't break it)
- `--json` on every command emits the raw envelope; keep it lossless.
- Real exit codes: 0 only on `status` ok/warning, non-zero otherwise.
- stdin (`-`) / `--file` / inline accepted for any text payload arg.
- Every destructive/mutating subcommand is gated by `--yes` and refuses
  off a TTY without it. New destructive commands MUST add the gate.
- One envelope shape across `jira` / `confluence` / `jenkins`.

## Groups & layout
- Native (edit here): `jira` / `confluence` / `jenkins` under `qactl/`.
- Vendored, delegated by `qactl/__main__.py` (don't refactor their
  internals to "match" — keep them liftable): `cli`/`nc`/`gnmi`/`rc`/
  `setup` (the `dnctl/` package) and `ixia` (`ixiactl/` + `ixia*/`).
  Fixes to those belong upstream conceptually; keep changes minimal and
  isolated to the vendored tree.

## Secrets
- NEVER commit credentials. All tokens resolve at runtime from the
  environment (`ATLASSIAN_*`, `JENKINS_*`). No `.env`, no defaults that
  embed a token, none in code/docstrings/tests/issues.

## Issues (gh)
- Bugs/change requests arrive as `gh` issues. Triage on read: confirm
  the repro (command + exit code) before fixing.
- Work straight on `main`: fix, commit, push. Reference the issue in the
  commit (`Closes #N`) so it closes on push. Label `bug` /
  `enhancement` / `needs-info`.

## Commits
- Work directly on `main` — no worktrees, no per-issue branches, no PRs.
  Keep `main` releasable: commit only green, focused work.
- Small, focused, imperative subjects ≤72 chars referencing the issue:
  `fix: gate jira comment delete on --yes (#4)`.

## Push / releases
- Commit and push directly to `main`. No force-push to `main`.
- Tag `vX.Y.Z` after notable changes and bump the version the CLI
  reports.

## Don't
- No edits outside this repo. No secrets anywhere. No `--no-verify`.
